physical environments. We also present studies related to technologies that are used in virtual spaces in order to support creativity. This last kind of technology seems to be more and more promising in the actual societal context, which requires remote working, all the more so during the current health crisis. More specifically, we discuss how virtual environments, particularly those from multiplayer games, not only redesign the way individuals work but can also contribute to enhancing creativity. Finally, we suggest perspectives towards the development of innovative new tools that aim to enhance creative performance in individual and collective situations.", "\"/><meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://sciendo-parsed-data-feed.s3.eu-central-1.amazonaws.com/612ea2dd1000020b549d6272/cover-image.jpg\"/><meta name=\"citation_title\" content=\"Technologies for Supporting Creativity in Design: A View of Physical and Virtual Environments with Regard to Cognitive and Social Processes\"/><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Karima Toumi\"/><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Fabien Girandola\"/><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Nathalie Bonnardel\"/><meta name=\"citation_publication_date\" content=\"2021/06/01\"/><meta name=\"citation_journal_title\" content=\"Creativity. Theories \u2013 Research - Applications\"/><meta name=\"citation_volume\" content=\"8\"/><meta name=\"citation_issue\" content=\"1\"/><meta name=\"citation_firstpage\" content=\"189\"/><meta name=\"citation_lastpage\" content=\"212\"/><meta name=\"citation_pdf_url\" content=\"https://www.sciendo.com/pdf/10.2478/ctra-2021-0012\"/><script async=\"\" src=\"https://badge.dimensions.ai/badge.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script><script src=\"https://crossmark-cdn.crossref.org/widget/v2.0/widget.js\"></script><script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"//s7.addthis.com/js/300/addthis_widget.js#pubid=ra-6048be7b4c38021f\"></script><script type=\"text/javascript\">var addthis_config = {", "           